                                    </dimensions>
                                </extent>
                                <foliation>
                                    <p>The manuscript is provided with a foliation from 1-43 and a
                                        number of columns from 1-170.</p>
                                </foliation>
                                <condition>
                                    <p>The manuscript is fragmentary. Of fol. 1 only the inner half
                                        is extant and the lower part is also cut away. Fol. 2 and 43
                                        are also damaged by cutting. Some of the outer margin of
                                        fol. 5 has been cut away, and several leaves have small
                                        holes and stains.</p>
                                </condition>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout columns="2" writtenLines="37 38">
                                    <p>The manuscript is written in double columns with 37 or 38
                                        lines per column. A few exceptions of 36 or 39 lines per
                                        column occur. Rubrics in red. Majuscules occur in red, blue,
                                        violet and green. Some of the majuscules have a red
                                        flourishing.</p>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
